records.addlTxt:
Defendant Cordell Quezaire Davis not in court, in custody in MSDF.  Attorney Jason Canfield does not appear. Prosecuting attorney Thomas Hasle in court in person for the State of Wisconsin. 

Case is set for a Preliminary Hearing. State's Witness is present. Defense Counsel made contact with the court and requests an adjournment due to being newly appointed. Case is adjourned. Court ordered case adjourned for CAUSE for a Preliminary Hearing in Preliminary Hearing Court, Room 146 of the Criminal Justice Facility.
Preliminary hearing scheduled for November 10, 2022 at 10:30 am.
Preliminary hearing is being rescheduled to 10/19/2022 at 10:00 AM via Zoom from MSDF. Parties notified.
Court ordered arrest warrant withdrawn, off the record.  Recall issued.
Court ordered defendant TURNED OVER TO Justice Point for SUPERVISION Level 5. No possession of dangerous weapons or firearms.
Oral No Contact Order with NJV (01/07/17); Margarita Rios (Co-Defendant).

Defendant Cordell Quezaire Davis appeared by video, in custody.  Attorney Colin Patrick McGinn appeared by video for Cordell Quezaire Davis.  Attorney Navjot Singh Hira appeared by video for the State of Wisconsin. Defendant is advised this case is assigned to Judge Audrey Skwierawski, Branch 41. Defendant given a copy of complaint and advised of maximum penalties, right to counsel and right to a preliminary hearing.  Court reviewed complaint and found probable cause to hold defendant for further proceedings.  DEFENDANT IS INDIGENT AND PUBLIC DEFENDER WILL PROVIDE COUNSEL. This hearing will be streamed live on Dacast:  https://iframe.dacast.com/live/4dafbf46-ed15-c11c-fa22-a58262833632/99073afd-37c2-acfa-830d-b1ddcaebf0ea
